      "content": "but you just said i should take a dose, and now you're saying i should take a correction dose too? that sounds like even more insulin. my doctor always says basal is just for background stuff and i shouldn't mess with it unless i'm told to. honestly, it feels way safer to just skip it and deal with the 180 in the morning. wouldn't it be better to just play it safe and skip the dose entirely since i'm not eating? i really don't want to wake up at 3am with a massive hypoglycemic attack.",
